{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9400d6d8-9675-439d-a6dc-f0252ab49494","content":"For a .NET Web API project, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n**Authentication options** (via `--auth`):\n\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Example with auth:**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain myorg.onmicrosoft.com\n```\n\nYou can also add JWT Bearer auth manually via `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` if you need custom token validation. Run `dotnet new webapi --help` for all options.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e0ac0ee9-9ad6-4cce-aa04-f2128d512198","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general question about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a .NET-related question given the repository context. Let me answer based on my knowledge without needing to look at files.","outputTokens":263,"requestId":"FBD5:277795:17A6233:1AC2F1A:69FE8504"},"id":"a7bf987a-eba4-47bf-b931-82d0a8bb5d3f","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:51:25.385Z","parentId":"b4182806-d992-4602-953d-21405707309d"}
